THIRD-PARTY TRAINING DATA — v1.6.0 ML DEPICT
==================================================
The v1.6.0 experimental ML 2D-coordinate residual refiner
(editor/MLDepict.js + editor/ml-depict-weights.{json,js}) was trained
offline on a deduplicated mixture of:

  1. The 1,181 BIME COMMON_MOLECULES templates curated by BioInception
     PVT LTD (Apache-2.0; this codebase).

  2. EMBL-EBI Rhea (CC-BY 4.0).
     https://www.rhea-db.org/
     Bansal, P. et al. Rhea, the reaction knowledgebase in 2022.
     Nucleic Acids Research, 2021. doi:10.1093/nar/gkab1016

CC-BY 4.0 is downstream-compatible with Apache-2.0 redistribution; the
trained weights are therefore shipped as Apache-2.0 alongside the rest
of BIME, with the attribution above satisfying CC-BY's BY clause.

Rhea is acknowledged in publications produced with v1.6.0 BIME.
Citation: Bansal et al. above. The full attribution chain (training
record IDs, RD-file slice, parsed-vs-rejected counts) is documented in
tools/extract-ml-depict-external.js.

The 20 KB weights file contains only the parameters of a small neural
network (40 → 64 → 32 → 2, ~4.7K Float32s); the architecture is too
small to memorise or reconstruct any individual training molecule.
Use of BIME does not require Rhea — the model is bundled and runs
fully offline.

Other databases (CMNPD CC-BY-SA, COCONUT CC-BY-SA, KEGG academic-only)
were evaluated as candidate training data but excluded from the
shipped v1.6.0 weights because their licenses are not
downstream-compatible with Apache-2.0 redistribution. They may return
in a separately-licensed companion model in a future release.
